3ad158db-91b2-44db-b4fa-160914e2d36b.30fe5a52-b177-4f7e-b5f3-584d0500e257.description=
Checks to see if a list contains every element in another list.

Inputs\:
sublist -The contained list.
container - The containing list.
delimiter - A delimiter separating elements in the two lists. Default is a comma
ignoreCase - If set to 'True' then the compare is not case sensitive. Default is True

Responses\:
true - sublist is contained in container.
false - sublist is not contained in container.

Results\:
Result - All items contained in the sublist that are not in the container.
3ad158db-91b2-44db-b4fa-160914e2d36b.5d36f739-51f6-4822-9743-d237f12e405a.description=
Checks if a number or word is equal to another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
value1 \=\= value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
3ad158db-91b2-44db-b4fa-160914e2d36b.8f7c7158-9c6a-4131-9d51-274f33845dec.description=
Clears the value of a flow variable

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to clear

Responses\:
success - cleared the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, null];
3ad158db-91b2-44db-b4fa-160914e2d36b.description=Starts the Parallel executions of the given flow in OO central based on the input list. 
Inputs\:
    workflowName 	- Name of the workflow to check.
    list - Comma Seprated list 
            Ex\: List of emails.
    numOfInstancesPerRun	- number of instances can run at same time.
    centralFlowPath 	- UUID or Complete Path of the flow in Central 
    flowInputName 	- Name of the input variable to pass the list values.


Results\:
    failedItems	- Number of list items failed
    successfullItems	- Number of list items successfull


Responses\:
    success 	- Opration executed successfully.
3ad158db-91b2-44db-b4fa-160914e2d36b.e5497dfe-1cd5-43c5-ad49-facc5ac31e50.description=
This operation does not do anything. It can be used to filter flow variables by defining them as inputs and filtering them in the Results tab.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
